# {{US|transportation}} A kind of rail passenger transport with a dedicated [[right of way]], usually for [[commuter]] transportation, powered by electricity, and with lower construction costs than traditional railroads.
#: ''The new Denver '''light rail''' runs along the Interstate highway.''

====Usage notes====
*[[streetcars|Streetcars]] did not have their own rights of way. Traditional railroad commuter lines would have high construction costs. [[interurban|Interurban]] electic railroads were not much used for commuter service. [[subway|Subways]] and other [[rapid transit]] also have high construction costs.

